      "message": "\u003eCan we count on |prefix| ending with a separator all the time?\nyes, that\u0027s how it\u0027s assigned.\n\n\u003eAlso, what is the problem with separators at a low level? Is it that if the if-statement below is checking if |mTempRootPrefix| is a prefix of |path|, and path is just |mTempRootPrefix| without the dir separator, the thing will incorrectly append?\nexactly. Also, on Windows we have two types of separators, and the last one might be different in prefix and path - so it\u0027s better to ignore it\n\n\u003eAnd then in all other cases, if |path| is some subdirectory or file inside of |mTempRootPrefix|, the dir separator should work, right? What if we did something like prefix \u003d\u003d StringView(path.c_str(), min(path.size(), prefix.size()) and not rely on the separator?\nwell, it would almost work: if we have a temp root as /root/\nand path \u003d /roo, min() would yield a match. But actually we should\u0027ve prepended /root/ to it.",
